Exception handling:
--------------------------------------------------------------------
what is exception:
       run time error or bug or defect
       it can be occur due to software or hardware
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Types of errors:
1)Syntactical Errors:
      These are errors raised dur to grammatical mistakes takes place in specific programming language.

2)Runtime Errors/Sematic Errors/Dynamic Errors:
       --These errors occur due to logical statements written in programming.
       --In order to handle runtime errors we have below statements:
       Try:
          try statements is allowed to define executable statements.

       Except:
             except statements will catch if any runtime errors occurred during try block execute statements.

       Finally:
               finally statement will execute its body of instructions irrespective of exception occurred.
